            </div>
            <div class="mano"><h2 class="d_heading">Names of the pathogens:</h2></div>
            <div>
                <ul class="d_paragraph">
                    <li>• Fusarium sessile</li>
                    <li>• algea</li>
                    <li>• fungi</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div><h2 class="d_heading">Symptoms:</h2></div>
            <div>
                <ul class="d_paragraph">
                    <li>• The appearance of brown and black gills is a notable symptom in Vannamei shrimp affected by black &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;gills disease.</li>
                    <li>• When there's enough oxygen in the pond, the shrimp swim on surface of water. You'll notice this when &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;we stop aeration.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div><h2 class="d_heading">Drawbacks Caused by the Disease in Shrimp Farming:</h2></div>
            <div>
                <ul class="d_paragraph">
                    <li>• Increased Risk of Shrimp Mortality.</li>
                    <li>• Buyers are not interested in purchasing shrimp that show signs of disease.</li>
                    <li>• Even when buyers express interest, they tend to make purchases at a lower cost.</li>
                    <li>• The amount of shrimp we can produce will go down because of mortlity.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div><h2 class="d_heading">Precautions:</h2></div>
            <div>
                <ul class="d_paragraph">
                    <li>• Enhance pond health by using bottom probiotics for effective bottom management.</li>
                    <li>• Reduce feed waste in the pond by regular monitoring.</li>
                    <li>• Keep the right amount of salinity and oxygen in the water.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div><h2 class="d_heading">Treatment:</h2></div>
            <div>
                <ul class="d_paragraph">
                    <li>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;We need to identify the cause of the disease. If it's due to pathogens, antibiotics are necessary. 
                        In cases where poor bottom and water quality are contributing factors, employ bottom probiotics for 
                        effective bottom management and consider water exchange. For issues related to ammonia and nitrate, 
                        utilize ammonia removers like zeolite alongside proper feed management for favorable results.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <div><p class="d_paragraph">**We need to make fast decisions because there's a high chance of mortality.**</p></div>
